    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Thanks a lot! yes, this is it. actually the most satisfactory method I found is from SO InoDB (https://stackoverflow.com/users/1894184/inodb)\r\n\r\n>> a=pd.DataFrame({\"var1\":\"a,b,c d,e,f\".split(),\"var2\":[1,2]})\r\n>> s = a.var1.str.split(\",\").apply(pd.Series, 1).stack()\r\n>> s.index = s.index.droplevel(-1)\r\n>> del a['var1']\r\n>> a.join(s)\r\n   var2 var1\r\n0     1    a\r\n0     1    b\r\n0     1    c\r\n1     2    d\r\n1     2    e\r\n1     2    f\r\n\r\n(I came up with the stack and before, I was not good with reindexing and joining)\r\n\r\nBut anyway a general purpose function with adjustable setting will be nice. Thanks!"
